c5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Nbd2 d5 6. c3 {Now, we shall take a look at Black's different
attempts to bother the f4-bishop.} Nh5 {This move was quite popular a few
years ago. Now White found some decent ways to fight for an advantage.} ({
Another way to apply the same idea is} 6... cxd4 7. exd4 Nh5 8. Be3 Bd6 9. Ne5
g6 10. Nd3 $5 ({It was considered that only} 10. g4 Ng7 11. h4 $44 {can be
dangerous for Black. Nowadays White is frequently choosing more conventional
