planning to develop the bishop via g2. In this way, it will be very difficult
for Black to expand in the centre by means of ...f7-f6 followed by ...e6-e5.} (
{After} 11. Be2 Ng7 12. O-O Nf5 13. Bf4 Bxf4 14. Nxf4 Qd6 15. g3 f6 $132 {
Black gets a decent counterplay.} (15... Bd7 16. Re1 $14 {1-0 (56) Nihal,S 
