Nd2 c5 4. Ngf3 cxd4 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Bc4 Qd7 7. O-O Nc6 8. Nb3 Nf6 9. Nbxd4 Nxd4
10. Nxd4 a6 11. Re1 Qc7 12. Bf1 Be7 13. Qf3 O-O 14. Bf4 Bd6 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 16.
Rad1 Qc7 17. Qg3 Qxg3 18. hxg3 {[#] All of this has been played in many games.
White is better centralized here compared to our main game, so he has some
basis to keep playing for an advantage.} Bd7 19. Nf3 {The best square for the
knight is e5, for the bishop - f3. Then, White should gradually push his
