{[#] Giri played inaccurate} 31. Ne1 $6 {in the game.} ({It was essential to
take control over d5-square, either with} 31. c4 f5 32. b4 $16) ({or a
positional pawn sacrifice:} 31. d5 $5 exd5 32. Nfd4 g6 33. g4 $16 {which looks
very appealing because black pieces are completely stuck and his pawns are
very weak.}) 31... Nb8 $6 {Too passive.} ({The right move was} 31... d5 $1 $14
{improving the pawn structure. Black could then focus on kingside play with ...
g5, ...f5, etc. to offset the weakness on b6.}) 32. Na7 $1 {Now the knight is
stuck on b8 and Black cannot push ...d5 any more.} Bd8 33. Nc2 Ke7 34. Nb4 $16
{Giri went on to win an instructive endgame based on the b6-weakness.} 1-0

