{[#] Caruana played} 30... Na5 $1 {"The knight goes to b3 to prepare the
powerful ...a5 and ...b4. White has great difficulty defending against this
and will struggle to make use of his clumsy rooks." - F. Caruana.} ({It is
tempting to start with} 30... a5 31. Be4 b4 32. axb4 axb4 33. Ra2 $132 {
but this is an inferior version of the ...b4-pawn break for Black since White
keeps the a-file under control.}) 31. Rad1 Nb3 32. Be3 a5 33. Be4 b4 34. axb4
axb4 35. Bxd5 Rxd5 36. Bf2 Ra8 $15 {Black took control over the only open file
and continued to press his advantage deep into the endgame.} 0-1

