{In the structure with doubled f-pawns, one of White's dreams is to take
control of the squares d4 and e5 after an exchange of his d-pawn for the
opponent's c-pawn. In this position, Black's positional threat is ...cxd4. In
this case, White will be forced to recapture on d4 with a pawn. We already
know that this is not a desirable scenario for White. Therefore, White's best
idea is} 9. dxc5 $1 Qxc5 10. Bd3 {Now, when the d4-square is available for one
of the knights, White has a structural advantage. At the same time, the
d3-bishop is clearly superior to its colleague. In order to establish a
blockade on the dark squares, White must exchange the c6-knight. The game
continued} O-O 11. O-O Re8 12. Ne5 $1 {[%cal Gd1e2,Gd2f3] We can see the
advantage of having a pawn on f4. White can increase the pressure by means of
Qe2 followed by Ndf3, thus achieving an extremely favourable French type of
position.} Nxe5 $2 {This is an obvious positional mistake. The e5-pawn would
provide a huge space advantage.} ({Nevertheless, even after} 12... Qb6 13. Rb1
Bd7 14. Qe2 $16 {[%cal Gd2f3] White is clearly better.}) 13. fxe5 Nd7 ({After} 
13... Ne4 14. Qa4 Bd7 15. Nxe4 dxe4 16. Qxe4 $16 {White enjoys a healthy extra
pawn.}) 14. Qe2 Qb6 15. Nf3 {[%cal Gf3d4,Ga1e1,Gd3b1] Black's position is
strategically hopeless. White's attack plays itself. His next moves will be
Nd4 followed by Rae1, Bb1 and Qc2. Black has no counterplay whatsoever.} h6 16.
Rae1 Nc5 17. Bb1 Bd7 18. Nd4 a6 19. h4 {[%cal Ge2c2] Once again, the h-pawn
enters the fight. After provoking ...g7-g6 with Qc2, White will be ready to
answer ...g7-g6 with h4-h5.} Qd8 20. Qc2 f5 21. exf6 Qxf6 22. Qh7+ Kf8 23. Re3
$18 {White has already a winning attack. In the game, Hamitevici converted his
advantage without problems.} Ke7 24. Nf5+ Kd8 25. Nxg7 Re7 26. Qg8+ Be8 27.
Nxe8 Rxe8 28. Qg4 Kc7 29. Rf3 Qe5 30. Rf7+ Nd7 31. Qa4 b5 32. Qa5+ Kc6 33. c4
Qxb2 34. cxd5+ exd5 35. Bf5 Nb6 36. Rb1 Qe5 37. Rc1+ Nc4 38. Bd7+ Kc5 39. Bxe8
Qxe8 40. Rf6 Qe5 41. Qa3+ b4 42. Qa5+ Kd4 43. Rd1+ Ke4 44. Rf4+ 1-0

