{[#]} 18... Nxd2 $1 {This strong move allows Black to exchange the
light-squared bishops via a6. The next few moves are quite logical.} 19. Qxd2
Ba6 $1 20. Nf2 Bxd3 21. Qxd3 Qc7 {[%cal Ga8b8,Gb6b5]} 22. Rfe1 Rab8 $1 {
[%cal Gb6b5] After neutralizing White's initiative, Black starts preparing his
queenside play. He is ready to proceed with ...b6-b5. White should already
fight for equality.} (22... Rab8 23. Re2 b5 24. axb5 Rxb5 25. Qd1 Qb7 26. Ra2
cxd4 27. exd4 Rxc3 28. bxc3 Rb1 29. Rxa5 Rxd1+ 30. Nxd1 h6 31. Rb2 Qe7 32. Nf2
Nc4 33. Ra8+ Kh7 34. Re2 Qf6 35. g3 g5 36. Ng4 Qf5 37. Ne5 gxf4 38. Nxc4 dxc4
39. Ra7 Qb1+ 40. Kg2 Kg6 41. gxf4 Qd3 42. Kf1 Qxc3 43. f5+ exf5 44. Rg2+ Kh5
45. Rxf7 Qd3+ 46. Ke1 c3 47. Rf2 Qb1+ 48. Ke2 Qa2+) 0-1

