{[#]} 1... cxd4 $1 {You should always consider this exchange when White cannot
recapture with the e-pawn. Now, the open c-file will make Black's queenside
play very effective.} 2. cxd4 O-O 3. Bd3 b6 {[%cal Gc8a6] With this move,
Black prepares the exchange of the light-squared bishops via a6. This exchange
is highly favourable for Black in the Stonewall structure.} *

