{This structure is favourable for White since he managed to occupy the
d4-square with a piece. Instead of immediately exchanging the bishops, White
played the precise} 13. Qe2 $1 {indicating that he will exchange the bishops
on his own terms.} Bxd3 14. cxd3 $1 $16 {A thematic recapture. Now, Black does
not have his usual slight pressure against the c2-pawn. Since White is better
developed, he is the one who will take advantage of the c-file. Additionally,
the d3-pawn is very strong in such structures. It controls both e4 and
c4-squares.} 1-0

