{[#]} 9. a5 $1 {As we already know, when Black has played ...a7-a6, fixing the
structure with a4-a5 is a good idea.} Qa7 $6 (9... Qd8 {was certainly a bit
more natural.}) 10. c3 e6 {At this point, the most natural follow-up would
have been} 11. h3 $5 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 b5 13. axb6 Qxb6 {The b3-knight is not as
vulnerable as it looks.} 14. Qd1 {White has a bishop pair and a better pawn
structure.} 1-0

