1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Nd2 c5 5. c3 Nc6 6. Bd3 Be7 {The current
theory considers the systems with an immediate Be7 very passive.} 7. Ngf3 O-O
8. Ne5 Qb6 9. Qb1 {another important idea in those structures is "Qb1" The
queen is attacking "h7" and protecting "b2"} Re8 $6 {the rook has nothing to
do on "e8"} 10. h4 {I am sure that you already remember this thematic idea.
After AlphaZero's games, we know that "h4" is almost always a possible plan}
cxd4 11. exd4 Qd8 12. Ndf3 {[%cal Rh1h3,Rh3g3]} h6 13. g4 {After h7-h6, White
almost always opens the game with "g4-g5"} Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Nd7 15. g5 (15. Bh7+ {
was faster} Kf8 16. Nxf7 Kxf7 17. Qg6+ Kf8 18. O-O-O $18 {[%csl Rg4][%cal
Rg4g5]}) 15... Nxe5 16. dxe5 hxg5 (16... h5 {was the last attempt to keep the
kingside closed} 17. g6 $1 $16) 17. hxg5 Bxg5 18. Qc1 Bxf4 19. Qxf4 f5 20.
O-O-O Bd7 21. Rdg1 {This is an absolute model attack - four pieces against a
single king} Re7 22. Qh4 Qf8 23. Be2 g6 24. Rxg6+ Rg7 25. Rf6 1-0

